 Thursday, August 14, 2008 
 
  
 
 To All My Students from IS 93 
 
  
 
 For those of you who have not heard, I will not be returning to the school this year as your Science teacher. Although it was a tough decision and many of you will be missed, I was offered a really great opportunity at Pan American International High School in Elmhurst, Queens. I will be teaching Biology as well as getting a brand new laboratory. As a Science teacher these chances do not come up often and one I could not pass up.  Don't worry as I'm sure my replacement will be fine and I will always be here if you need me. After this year you will be going into high school and hopefully you come and visit my website from time to time to get some material to help you. Please keep in touch, I would like to know how all of you are doing. If you have any questions don't hesitate to ask. And feel free to still use my blog for extra credit, maybe I can convince Ms. S. to give you guys credit for it.  Best of luck, Mr. R.  mrriccardo@optonline.net  
  
 
 
 

